{
  "analysis": "The previous autotune failed because `accuracy` is not a valid fastText autotune metric. The valid metric is `f1` or `f1:labelname`. Prepared lowercased/whitespace-normalized data exists at `/app/work/train.txt` and `/app/work/test.txt`, with a 630k/20k autotune split at `/app/work/train_aut.txt` and `/app/work/val_aut.txt`. The best model so far was only 0.579 local accuracy and 47MB, so accuracy still needs improvement. I will run fastText autotune with the valid `f1` metric and a 140MB model-size constraint to keep the output under 150MB. Autotune should explore hyperparameters and quantization automatically. I will start it in the background and poll for progress/completion.",
  "plan": "1. Remove failed autotune artifacts to start clean.\n2. Start background fastText autotune with `-autotune-metric f1`, `-autotune-duration 900`, `-autotune-modelsize 140000000`, softmax loss, and all CPUs.\n3. Poll for about 5.5 minutes to confirm it started and monitor progress. Later batches will wait/evaluate after autotune completes.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "rm -f /app/work/model_aut.bin /app/work/model_aut.vec /app/work/model_aut.ftz /app/work/autotune.log /app/work/autotune.pid\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup /opt/fastText/fasttext supervised -input /app/work/train_aut.txt -output /app/work/model_aut -autotune-validation /app/work/val_aut.txt -autotune-metric f1 -autotune-duration 900 -autotune-modelsize 140000000 -loss softmax -thread $(nproc) > /app/work/autotune.log 2>&1 &\necho $! > /app/work/autotune.pid\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "for i in $(seq 1 10); do\n  pid=$(cat /app/work/autotune.pid 2>/dev/null || true)\n  if [ -n \"$pid\" ] && [ -d \"/proc/$pid\" ]; then status=running; else status=finished; fi\n  size=$(stat -c %s /app/work/model_aut.bin 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n  printf 'iter=%s status=%s bin_size=%s ' \"$i\" \"$status\" \"$size\"\n  tail -1 /app/work/autotune.log 2>/dev/null || true\n  if [ \"$status\" = finished ] && [ \"$size\" -gt 0 ]; then echo 'autotune_done_break'; break; fi\n  sleep 30\ndone\n",
      "duration": 330.0
    }
  ]
}
